SIMPLE: nutriment
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Nutriment
<hw>Nu"tri*ment</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>nutrimentum</ets>, fr. <ets>nutrire</ets> to nourish. See
<er>Nourish</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>That which nourishes; a nutrient; anything which
promotes growth and repairs the natural waste of animal or vegetable
life; food; aliment.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The stomach returns what it has received, in strength and
<qex>nutriment</qex> diffused into all parts of the body.</q>
<rj><qau>South.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>That which promotes development or growth.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Is not virtue in mankind⟦br⟧
The <qex>nutriment</qex> that feeds the mind?</q>
<rj><qau>Swift.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Nutrimental</ent>⟦br⟧
